Title : Nele Neuhaus
Text : {{expand language|topic=|langcode=DE|otherarticle=Nele Neuhaus|date=September 2014}}
[[File:Nele Neuhaus 2016.jpg|thumb|Nele Neuhaus, 2016]]
'''Cornelia Neuhaus''' (born 20 June 1967 in [[Münster]] as Cornelia Löwenberg) is a [[Germany|German]] [[writer]].
She is best known for her crime thrillers set in the [[Taunus]] near [[Frankfurt]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.crimefictionlover.com/2013/04/snow-white-must-die/|title=Snow White Must Die » CRIME FICTION LOVER|website=www.crimefictionlover.com|access-date=2016-08-14}}</ref>

She has also published romantic novels under her maiden name Löwenberg, as well as horse stories for teenagers.

==Bibliography==
* ''Unter Haien (Swimming With Sharks)''
* ''Sommer der Wahrheit'' (as Nele Löwenberg)
* ''Straße nach Nirgendwo'' (as Nele Löwenberg)

===Bodenstein/Kirchhoff series===
* ''Eine unbeliebte Frau''
* ''Mordsfreunde''
* ''Tiefe Wunden (The Ice Queen)''
* ''Schneewittchen muss sterben (Snow White Must Die)''
* ''Wer Wind sät''
* ''Böser Wolf (Bad Wolf / Big Bad Wolf)''
* ''Die Lebenden und die Toten (I Am Your Judge / To Catch a Killer)''
* ''Im Wald''
* ''Muttertag''

== Further reading ==
* Oliver Mayer: ''Popular German Crime Fiction: Nele Neuhaus and her Bestselling Novels''; In: Studies in Foreign Languages & Literature, Vol. 50, p.&nbsp;45-60. [http://hdl.handle.net/10424/00007176 Link to full text]

